-- Canada to Name David Johnston of Waterloo as Governor-General, Globe Says
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-07-08T11:18:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/canada-to-name-david-johnston-of-waterloo-as-governor-general-globe-says.html

          
          
             Canada will name University of
Waterloo President David Johnston as the countryâ€™s new Governor-
General today, the Globe and Mail reported, citing unidentified
people.  
 Johnston, 69, will replace  Michaelle Jean  when her term
ends in September, the newspaper said. Johnston was chosen by a
special committee appointed by Canadian Prime Minister  Stephen Harper .  
 The announcement will come two days after  Queen Elizabeth II  finished her tour of Canada. The Queen must give her blessing
before a new Governor-General is chosen, the newspaper said.  
